@abtink I think this tool is mainly for OpenThread users, who might still use a very old version of OpenThread(I used to find this fact in some questions raised in openthread-users group).  And once they want to upgrade to the latest OpenThread, they will find it difficult. That's why I think it makes sense to provide and maintain a script to migrate old code to latest code.

Although we don't support any of the older config definitions, we still provided `openthread-config-default-check.h` to check those old definitions are not defined. That's helpful to report a problem. But If I am an OpenThread user, I would wish to have a tool to help me solve the problem if possible. I was just asked to help migrate https://github.com/openthread/silk, I find this tool is very helpful.

So I tend to maintain this script, and every time we make a change, we should update this script to migrate the code. This also helps us to do GitHub sync. Thoughts?

