@librasungirl 

From my point of view, I also don't understand why it's designed in this way. `Type/Average Enum` and `Metric Enum` doesn't work in a combination way. For example, when `Metric Enum` is 0(PDUs Received), then `Type/Average Enum` has to be 0(Count/summation). Otherwise it's meaningless(we won't calculate count with exponential moving average). And vice versa for other `Metric Enum`. 

So the current fact is that we can always infer `Type/Average Enum` from `Metric Enum`. `Type/Average Enum` isn't quite useful for now. We can add some check to see if the two fields match. Perhaps in extensions in the future, the two fields could work in a combination way. I think for now the usage of `Type/Average Enum` is just a information for the user about how the metrics is calculated(though it's already implied by `Metric Enum`).

