I'd prefer keeping this closer in name to the API in [TypeScript](https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/06d4dde8898b2a0de2c3c7ff8e45f97495b89d82/sdk/nodejs/config.ts#L185)/[Python](https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/06d4dde8898b2a0de2c3c7ff8e45f97495b89d82/sdk/python/lib/pulumi/config.py#L178).

```typescript
public getObject<T>(key: string): T | undefined
```

```python
def get_object(self, key: str) -> Optional[Any]:
```

Why can't it be something like this (I have not tried it):

```c#
public T? GetObject<T>(string key)
{
    var v = Get(key);

    try
    {
        return v == null ? null : JsonSerializer.Deserialize<T>(v);
    }
    catch (JsonException ex)
    {
        throw new ConfigTypeException(FullKey(key), v, typeof(T).FullName, ex);
    }
}
```

That way, you can do things like:

```c#
var servers = config.GetObject<string[]>("servers");
```

...without having to manually parse the `JsonDocument`.

I'm also wary of having `JsonDocument` in our public API. Feels too close to `XmlDocument` for me (which fell out of favor and made APIs that included it in public signatures essentially legacy). Who knows when Microsoft will favor yet another API for parsing JSON in the future. If we don't tie ourselves to the types, we can easily swap out the implementation.

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/design-guidelines/system-xml-usage

> **X DO NOT** use `XmlNode` or `XmlDocument` to represent XML data. Favor using instances of `IXPathNavigable`, `XmlReader`, `XmlWriter`, or subtypes of `XNode` instead. `XmlNode` and `XmlDocument` are not designed for exposing in public APIs.

Also, we cannot subclass from `FileNotFoundError` (because it wasn't) as it changes observable behavior, such as

```
try:
    with open(input) as file:
        output = cxxfilt.demangle(file.read())
except FileNotFoundError:
    print(input, 'not found')
except cxxfilt.InvalidName:
    print(input, 'invalid')
else:
    print(output)
```

